data.description: ***Owner is scheduled to put in new carpet in rear spare bedroom and a new floor in the half bath. Welcome to this inviting home, situated in a prime location. Nestled just 6 miles away from the convenience of I95, Spotsylvania Towne Centre, and Central Park, you'll find yourself only a 15-minute drive from both the highway and bustling shopping centers. Plus, Old Towne Fredericksburg is a mere 25-minute drive away, offering the best of both worlds - a tranquil home base and easy access to all the attractions. Step inside through the front door, and you'll be greeted by a living room that flows into the kitchen and an inviting eat-in kitchen area. The kitchen has stainless steel appliances, and a window over the sink provides an enjoyable view of your backyard. Adjacent to the kitchen, step out the back door leading to a generously sized deck, overlooking a flat, and fenced backyard. Enjoy sunny days in the comfort of the shade thanks to the electric awning on the deck. As you venture down the hallway, you'll come across a laundry closet equipped with a washer and dryer for your convenience. Further along, a full bathroom awaits. The two spare bedrooms have ample storage space, with large closets for all your belongings. The primary bedroom features a convenient half bath and a walk-in closet. Key updates to this lovely home include new windows just five years ago, a replacement water heater only two years ago, and a new heat pump installed three years ago. The roof is approximately ten years old. You won’t want to miss this opportunity to live in a pleasant community close to so many of Fredericksburg’s many amenities. Property is sold As Is; inspections for informational purposes only.
